      "writtenOn": "2020-02-24T23:02:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it is ok at this level of abstraction because this is exactly what spanner package is doing: calling a callback.\n\nmore specifically, yes, i think its ok in the context of tasks. we don\u0027t want to buffer because it partially defeats the purpose. I am not aware of problems caused by keeping a RO txn open for a long time. Spanner keeps timestamped versions/snapshots of its state for 24h. This TXN will read the state from that snapshot.",
